Is the PS3 Linux based or not?. If it is that should mean that the PS3 doesn't fragment files. Does anyone know for sure?
PS3 and PS4 OSes are all FreeBSD based, and AFAIK they use UFS2 file system, which has built in features to prevent file fragmentation if that answers your question.
